# ⚙️ Environment Variables

Create `.env` file:

DATABASE_URL="postgresql://postgres:postgres@localhost:5432/feedbackdb"
JWT_SECRET="your_secret_key"
PORT=3001

Docker environment:

DATABASE_URL="postgresql://postgres:postgres@feedback-db:5432/feedbackdb"

---

# 🛠 Installation & Setup

## 1. Install dependencies

```bash
npm install
```

---

## 2. Configure environment variables

Create a `.env` file:

```env
DATABASE_URL="postgresql://postgres:postgres@localhost:5432/feedbackdb"
JWT_SECRET="your_secret_key"
PORT=3001
```

---

## 3. Run with Docker

Build and start containers:

```bash
docker compose up --build
```

Or run in background:

```bash
docker compose up -d
```

---

## 4. Run Prisma migrations

After containers are up, execute:

```bash
docker exec -it feedback-backend npx prisma migrate dev --name init
```

---

## 5. Generate Prisma Client

```bash
docker exec -it feedback-backend npx prisma generate
```

---

## 6. Seed admin user

```bash
docker exec -it feedback-backend node src/seed.js
```

This creates the default admin account:

- username: `admin`
- password: `1234`

---

## 7. Start the application

Development mode:

```bash
npm run dev
```

Production mode:

```bash
npm start
```

---

---

## Docker useful commands
Show running containers:

```bash
docker compose ps
```

Open a shell inside backend container:

```bash
docker exec -it feedback-backend sh
```

View logs:

```bash
docker logs feedback-backend
```

---

# ⚠️ Troubleshooting

If you encounter database-related errors or HTTP 500 responses, run:

```bash
docker exec -it feedback-backend npx prisma migrate dev --name init

docker exec -it feedback-backend npx prisma generate

node src/seed.js
```

These commands will:

1. Apply database migrations.
2. Generate Prisma Client.
3. Create the default admin user.


# 🌐 Browser URLs

After starting the application, open the following URLs in your browser:

## User Feedback Page

Submit feedback as a normal user:

```
http://localhost:3001/
```

---

## Admin Login Page

Login with admin credentials:

```
http://localhost:3001/login.html
```

Default credentials:

```
username: admin
password: 1234
```

---

## Admin Dashboard

After successful login, you will be redirected automatically to:

```
http://localhost:3001/admin.html
```

---

## API Base URL

```
http://localhost:3001
```

---

## Protected Admin API

```
GET    /feedback/admin/feedbacks
PATCH  /feedback/admin/feedbacks/:id
```

These endpoints require:

```
Authorization: Bearer <token>
```



# 📬 API Endpoints

## Auth
POST /auth/login

## User Feedback
POST /feedback

## Admin (Protected)
GET /feedback/admin/feedbacks
PATCH /feedback/admin/feedbacks/:id

Headers:
Authorization: Bearer <token>

---

# 📦 Postman

- Postman collection is included
- Base URL:
http://localhost:3001

No environment variables used in Postman.

---

# 🔐 Authentication Flow

1. User logs in via /auth/login
2. Token saved in localStorage
3. Token sent in Authorization header
4. Backend middleware validates token
5. Admin routes are protected

---

# ⚠️ Important Notes

## Prisma + Docker Issue Fix

If you get 500 errors:

npx prisma db push
npx prisma generate
node prisma/seed.js

